The paper deals with the problem of real-world image denoising, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The authors also mention the use of sparse or low rank theories, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.MM) and statistical learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves evaluating different denoising methods, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
